3. Definitions:
{
    "3. Definitions": [
        {
            "Original": "SNMPv2-PDU DEFINITIONS ::= BEGIN IMPORTS ObjectName, ObjectSyntax, Integer32 FROM SNMPv2-SMI; \\-- protocol data units PDUs ::= CHOICE { get-request GetRequest-PDU, get-next-request GetNextRequest-PDU, get-bulk-request GetBulkRequest-PDU, response Response-PDU, set-request SetRequest-PDU, inform-request InformRequest-PDU, snmpV2-trap SNMPv2-Trap-PDU, report Report-PDU, } \\-- PDUs GetRequest-PDU ::= [0] IMPLICIT PDU GetNextRequest-PDU ::= [1] IMPLICIT PDU Response-PDU ::= [2\"\")] IMPLICIT PDU SetRequest-PDU ::= [3\"\")] IMPLICIT PDU \\-- [4] is obsolete GetBulkRequest-PDU ::= [5\"\")] IMPLICIT BulkPDU InformRequest-PDU ::= [6] IMPLICIT PDU SNMPv2-Trap-PDU ::= [7] IMPLICIT PDU \\-- Usage and precise semantics of Report-PDU are not presently \\-- defined.",
            "Adjusted": "SNMPv2-PDU definitions begin with imports of ObjectName, ObjectSyntax, and Integer32 from SNMPv2-SMI. Protocol data units (PDUs) are defined as a choice of get-request GetRequest-PDU, get-next-request GetNextRequest-PDU, get-bulk-request GetBulkRequest-PDU, response Response-PDU, set-request SetRequest-PDU, inform-request InformRequest-PDU, snmpV2-trap SNMPv2-Trap-PDU, and report Report-PDU. GetRequest-PDU is defined as [0] IMPLICIT PDU, GetNextRequest-PDU as [1] IMPLICIT PDU, Response-PDU as [2] IMPLICIT PDU, SetRequest-PDU as [3] IMPLICIT PDU, GetBulkRequest-PDU as [5] IMPLICIT BulkPDU, InformRequest-PDU as [6] IMPLICIT PDU, and SNMPv2-Trap-PDU as [7] IMPLICIT PDU. The usage and precise semantics of Report-PDU are not presently defined."
        },
        {
            "Original": "Any SNMP administrative framework making use of \\-- this PDU must define its usage and semantics.",
            "Adjusted": "Any SNMP administrative framework making use of the Report-PDU must define its usage and semantics."
        },
        {
            "Original": "Report-PDU ::= [8] IMPLICIT PDU max-bindings INTEGER ::= 2147483647 PDU ::= SEQUENCE { request-id Integer32, error-status -- sometimes ignored INTEGER { noError(0), tooBig(1), noSuchName(2), -- for proxy compatibility badValue(3), -- for proxy compatibility readOnly(4), -- for proxy compatibility genErr(5), noAccess(6), wrongType(7), wrongLength(8), wrongEncoding(9), wrongValue(10), noCreation(11), inconsistentValue(12), resourceUnavailable(13), commitFailed(14), undoFailed(15), authorizationError(16), notWritable(17), inconsistentName(18) }, error-index -- sometimes ignored INTEGER (0..max-bindings), variable-bindings -- values are sometimes ignored VarBindList } BulkPDU ::= -- MUST be identical in SEQUENCE { -- structure to PDU request-id Integer32, non-repeaters INTEGER (0..max-bindings), max-repetitions INTEGER (0..max-bindings), variable-bindings -- values are ignored VarBindList } \\-- variable binding VarBind ::= SEQUENCE { name ObjectName, CHOICE { value ObjectSyntax, unSpecified -- in retrieval requests NULL, \\-- exceptions in responses noSuchObject[0] IMPLICIT NULL, noSuchInstance[1] IMPLICIT NULL, endOfMibView[2] IMPLICIT NULL } } \\-- variable-binding list VarBindList ::= SEQUENCE (SIZE (0..max-bindings)) OF VarBind END",
            "Adjusted": "Report-PDU is defined as [8] IMPLICIT PDU. max-bindings INTEGER is defined as 2147483647. PDU is defined as a sequence containing request-id Integer32, error-status INTEGER with values noError(0), tooBig(1), noSuchName(2), badValue(3), readOnly(4), genErr(5), noAccess(6), wrongType(7), wrongLength(8), wrongEncoding(9), wrongValue(10), noCreation(11), inconsistentValue(12), resourceUnavailable(13), commitFailed(14), undoFailed(15), authorizationError(16), notWritable(17), inconsistentName(18), error-index INTEGER (0..max-bindings), and variable-bindings VarBindList. BulkPDU is defined as a sequence containing request-id Integer32, non-repeaters INTEGER (0..max-bindings), max-repetitions INTEGER (0..max-bindings), and variable-bindings VarBindList. VarBind is defined as a sequence containing name ObjectName and a choice of value ObjectSyntax, unSpecified NULL, noSuchObject[0] IMPLICIT NULL, noSuchInstance[1] IMPLICIT NULL, or endOfMibView[2] IMPLICIT NULL. VarBindList is defined as a sequence of size (0..max-bindings) of VarBind."
        }
    ]
}

4. Protocol Specification -> 4.2. PDU Pr:
{
    "4. Protocol Specification -> 4.2. PDU Processing -> 4.2.3. The GetBulkRequest-PDU -> 4.2.3.1. Another Example of Table Traversal": [
        {
            "Original": "This example demonstrates how the GetBulkRequest-PDU can be used as an alternative to the GetNextRequest-PDU.",
            "Adjusted": "This example demonstrates how the GetBulkRequest-PDU can be used as an alternative to the GetNextRequest-PDU."
        },
        {
            "Original": "The same traversal of the IP net-to-media table as shown inSection 4.2.2.1 is achieved with fewer exchanges.",
            "Adjusted": "The same traversal of the IP net-to-media table as shown in Section 4.2.2.1 is achieved with fewer exchanges."
        },
        {
            "Original": "The SNMPv2 entity acting in a manager role begins by sending a GetBulkRequest-PDU with the modest max-repetitions value of 2, and containing the indicated OBJECT IDENTIFIER values as the requested variable names: GetBulkRequest [ non-repeaters = 1, max-repetitions = 2 ] ( sysUpTime, ipNetToMediaPhysAddress, ipNetToMediaType ) The SNMPv2 entity acting in an agent role responds with a Response-PDU: Response (( sysUpTime.0 = \"123456\" ), ( ipNetToMediaPhysAddress.1.9.2.3.4 = \"000010543210\" ), ( ipNetToMediaType.1.9.2.3.4 = \"dynamic\" ), ( ipNetToMediaPhysAddress.1.10.0.0.51 = \"000010012345\" ), ( ipNetToMediaType.1.10.0.0.51 = \"static\" )) The SNMPv2 entity acting in a manager role continues with: GetBulkRequest [ non-repeaters = 1, max-repetitions = 2 ] ( sysUpTime, ipNetToMediaPhysAddress.1.10.0.0.51, ipNetToMediaType.1.10.0.0.51 ) The SNMPv2 entity acting in an agent role responds with: Response (( sysUpTime.0 = \"123466\" ), ( ipNetToMediaPhysAddress.2.10.0.0.15 = \"000010987654\" ), ( ipNetToMediaType.2.10.0.0.15 = \"dynamic\" ), ( ipNetToMediaNetAddress.1.9.2.3.4 = \"9.2.3.4\" ), ( ipRoutingDiscards.0 = \"2\" )) This response signals the end of the table to the SNMPv2 entity acting in a manager role.",
